            <summary>[p]Physiognomia et chiromantia. 
[p]An owner's name has been erased on the first leaf, all now legible is 'Sum Iohannis..[Frei?]burgensis'. 
[p]Illustrated by numerous pen-drawings of hands and heads. 
[p]Fol. 1 (Begins) Chiromantia diuinationis species est, quae per / linearum manuum inspectionem celebratur... 2 Physignomia [sic] M Dani. / Recte Cicero hunc philosophum appellat ...44 ... uel torturam significat aut contractionem membrorum.</summary>
